    <statement><div><p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Solve the quadratic equation <m>{x^2-x-2}=0</m>. If there is a repeated root, enter this twice.</p>
<p><nowrap><m>x = </m> <fillin characters="5" name="ans1"/>  or <m>x = </m> <fillin characters="5" name="ans2"/><nowrap/></nowrap></p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><p>We are asked to factorise the quadratic equation <m>{x^2-x-2}=0.</m></p>
<p>First factorise the left-hand side:</p>
<p><me>{x^2-x-2}={\left(x-2\right) \left(x+1\right)}.</me></p>
<p>Equate each factor to zero to obtain the two solutions:</p>
<p>Solution 1: <m>x= {2}</m></p>
<p>Solution 2: <m>x= {-1}</m>.</p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>2</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>-1</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>